<item>
            <title>[LU-8181] lov_verify_lmm() wrong format for the argument type</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-8181</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In lov_verify_lmm() we have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;sprintf(buffer+2*i, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;%.2X&quot;&lt;/span&gt;, ((&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;char&lt;/span&gt; *)lmm)[i]);
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This produces a warning since we only reference char, but assume int in the format.&lt;br/&gt;
correct format is apparently %.2hhX&lt;/p&gt;</description>
